<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="28.[189,454,406,432]" box="[189,454,406,432]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,454,406,432]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,454,406,432]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[189,1399,454,554]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,587,454,480]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassata" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Floccocheila">
<emphasis box="[189,301,454,480]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[318,471,454,480]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Floccocheila</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[488,587,455,480]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">crassata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[594,684,455,481]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is more robust but otherwise similar to the Palearctic species 
<taxonomicName authority="(Harris, 1780)" baseAuthorityName="Harris" baseAuthorityYear="1780" box="[189,645,491,517]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="illustrata" subGenus="Floccocheila">
<emphasis box="[189,301,491,517]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[319,341,492,517]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">F.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[358,466,491,517]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">illustrata</emphasis>
(Harris, 1780)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[656,924,491,517]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassata" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Floccocheila">
<emphasis box="[656,768,491,517]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[786,808,492,517]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">F.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[825,924,492,517]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">crassata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[933,1024,492,518]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be discerned from all other members of subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov" authorityYear="2002" box="[452,605,528,554]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Floccocheila">
<emphasis box="[452,605,528,554]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Floccocheila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the distinctly protruded face.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="28.[189,324,595,621]" box="[189,324,595,621]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,595,621]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,595,621]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[189,1398,643,706]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
The specific epithet is from the Latin ‘ 
<emphasis box="[653,742,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">crassus</emphasis>
’ meaning ‘stout’, referring to the robust habitus of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
